    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "12 of 13 V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because ASTM F1717 is a prescriptive standard that defines a single canonical test configuration; clinical variability is addressed through separate fatigue and worst-case analyses outside this COU. Overall model credibility is sufficient for the intended regulatory use. Package conforms to ProfileMinimal; digital signature is pending completion of the organizational signature workflow and will be appended prior to final regulatory submission.",
